      "author": "dipro (Dipro Bhowmik)",
      "cookedHtml": "<p>Hey <a href=\"http://monday.com\">monday.com</a> community! <img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/apple/wave.png?v=12\" title=\":wave:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":wave:\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" /></p>\n<p>Our Zendesk integration is amazing for pulling new Zendesk tickets into a board, but what about existing ones? Well, I just posted an example on how to import Zendesk tickets into <a href=\"http://monday.com\">monday.com</a> with a Python script! <img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/apple/crystal_ball.png?v=12\" title=\":crystal_ball:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":crystal_ball:\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" /></p>\n<p>Check it out on Github here: <a href=\"https://github.com/yuhgto/mondaydotcom-import-example.py\" class=\"inline-onebox\">GitHub - yuhgto/mondaydotcom-import-example.py</a></p>\n<p>Enjoy <img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/apple/beers.png?v=12\" title=\":beers:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":beers:\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" /></p>"
